Only start accumulating *after* encountering the first non-zero remainder:

```java
public static int findSum(int k) {
    int sum = 0;
    boolean foundNonZero = false:
    for (; k != 0; k /= 10) {
        if (foundNonZero) {
            sum += (k % 10)*(k % 10);
        } else {
            foundNonZero = k % 10 != 0;
        }
    }
    return sum;
}
```

